examples.en: The prisoner's story was borne out by his wife.
The prisoner's arms were pinioned to his sides with ropes.
Doesn't the prisoner's story conflict with the known facts?
The guards savagely beat the prisoner's feet with a bastinado.
The prisoner's attempt to escape was foiled at the last minute.
The prisoner's opposition broke down under repeated questioning.
The captain went to the enemy camp to barter for the prisoner's life.
The prisoner's manacles abraded his wrists and ankles until they bled.
How many people have testified to the truth of the prisoner's statement?
All those years spent in prison have worn away the prisoner's resistance.
The prisoner's dilemma will induce people to behave in opportunistic ways.
